<subSubSection id="48D355CA8FD6FE5848F75138FE01F984" pageId="408" pageNumber="409" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="007606418FD6FE5848F75138FE01F984" blockId="408.[151,1437,151,1652]" pageId="408" pageNumber="409">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FD6FE5848F75138FE9EF9DC" bold="true" box="[199,315,1556,1580]" pageId="408" pageNumber="409">Remarks.</emphasis>
Mita &amp; Matsumoto (2012) have described for the first time the male of 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28FD6FE584C585138FB7BF9DC" baseAuthorityName="R. Perkins" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[1128,1246,1556,1580]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Gonatopus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="408" pageNumber="409" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="javanus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FD6FE584C585138FB7BF9DC" box="[1128,1246,1556,1580]" italics="true" pageId="408" pageNumber="409">G. javanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The association of the opposite sexes was determined with mitochondrial COI sequence (first application of this technique to sex association in dryinids).
</paragraph>
